				<h4 id="republish">I want to republish an image from CHLA. How do I get permission?</h4>
				<p>Mann Library does not own the rights to content found in the CHLA collection. Anything published in the United States before 1923 is in the public domain and does not require permission; however, if the image you wish to use was published in 1923 or later, you will need to determine the copyright status yourself.</p>
				<p>Whether public domain or with permission of the rights owner, if you do republish an image from the CHLA collection we ask that you attribute the provider of the image as "Image courtesy of the Core Historical Literature of Agriculture (CHLA), Ithaca, NY: Albert R. Mann Library, Cornell University."</p>
